1
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,840
Fine, then I won't return the shares.

2
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,920
-Mom!
-It's time for your medicine.

3
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:36,960
-Not now, Pong!
-Go away, Pong!

4
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:47,320
I'm not the type
to steal a friend's crush.

5
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,760
Fuang's my close friend.

6
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,600
If I had known,
I would've stayed away from him!

7
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,280
I'm speechless. I'm stunned, shocked,

8
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,960
and so happy!

9
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:58,960
Thank you.

10
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,800
But…

11
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:05,640
are you really sure
he will accept me as his assistant?

12
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:13,320
Go ahead and look. Take your time.
Look as long as you want.

13
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,600
Are you hungry?

14
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,240
Want some food? Are you thirsty?

15
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:19,840
I'll get you some water.
Or tea? Do you want coffee?

16
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:22,280
Maybe cookies?

17
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,280
Aunt Pim has some.

18
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,360
She also prepared mango
with sweet fish sauce. Want some?

19
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:27,520
Dad.

20
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:32,480
Dad.

21
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,280
What are you doing, Dad?

22
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:57,920
Cent!

23
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,080
What are you doing?

24
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,000
And what were you looking at just now?

25
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,280
I've never seen you dressed like this.

26
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,880
Well…

27
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:35,680
We've only met once.
Who would want you to see me like this?

28
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,640
So this is okay
for the second time we meet?

29
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:41,600
Hey! This is my house.

30
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,480
I dress like this at home.

31
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,720
What are you doing here?

32
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,720
Cent, here you go.

33
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,440
Thank you.

34
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,840
Dad!

35
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,360
Fuang.
What are you doing over there?

36
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,520
I'm not dressed properly, Dad.

37
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,400
Oh, okay.

38
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,360
Cent, want to watch some old films?

39
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:12,280
Someone's been scanning old film reels

40
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,760
and getting people to dub over them.

41
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:16,680
It's really well done. Interested?

42
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:19,360
Maybe next time. I need to head home.

43
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,560
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

44
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,640
What a shame. We were getting
into a good conversation.

45
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,760
Good conversation?

46
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,320
-What were you talking about?
-Young people stuff.

47
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,360
It's okay. I heard from Eiang
you've been busy lately.

48
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:38,360
Let's go. Fuang, watch this for me.

49
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,360
I'll walk you out.

50
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:43,680
Next time you come, let me know.
I've got tons more films.

51
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,800
-Have you ever watched old movies?
-Yes, I have.

52
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,920
You're already that close?

53
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:53,560
If there's any movie you want to watch,
just tell me. Don't be shy, okay?

54
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:54,760
Thank you very much.

55
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,600
Be prepared. No special treatment.

56
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,520
-See you tomorrow.
-Tomorrow?

57
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,280
See you tomorrow.

58
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,000
I promise I won't let you down.

59
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,160
-Don't be so confident.
-Don't be so confident.

60
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,800
Hey!

61
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,240
We're really on the same wavelength.

62
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,840
Go on, drive safely.

63
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:25,240
-We'll set it up.
-Of course. Thank you.

64
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,240
Yeah.

65
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,760
What?

66
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,920
You two got along that well?

67
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,560
Yeah! I've always wanted a son.

68
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,400
-Huh?
-Yeah!

69
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,160
You should get to work,

70
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,160
so all that big talk of yours
won't go to waste.

71
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,160
Alright?

72
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,200
-Dad!
-Don't embarrass me, okay?

73
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,560
Ugh!

74
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:07,320
NGOW FAMILY ASSOCIATION

75
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,360
Design team outfits
for a gaming competition?

76
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,400
Yes.

77
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:23,200
Like this. Please take a look.

78
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,320
Yuan, can you help me with this?

79
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,200
The organizer said
there's a 2,000 baht budget for costumes.

80
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,800
Alright then.

81
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,880
I'll design it. You can decide later
whether you like it or not.

82
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,000
Do you have any paper, pen, or pencil?

83
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Yes.

84
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,320
Okay.

85
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,760
Alright, let's do it.

86
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,680
Who drew this?

87
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,200
I drew it myself.

88
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,920
You've got talent.

89
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,640
Not bad at all.

90
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,280
Mom, do you like it?

91
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,160
Yeah, it's pretty good.

92
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:14,200
You want three sets of this design

93
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,720
-done by tomorrow?
-Yes.

94
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,600
Honestly, it's not that hard.

95
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:23,960
It can be done. But

96
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,920
who's going to sew it for you?

97
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
I already talked to Aunt Kai.

98
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,240
She'll do the sewing.

99
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,640
I'll do the cutting.

100
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,320
Just let me borrow
a sewing machine and this space.

101
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,160
I'll help too.

102
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,880
Please, Dad.

103
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:45,480
The shop has plenty of leftover fabric.

104
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:48,800
Just consider it helping the kids, okay?

105
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,400
-Dai!
-Yes, Uncle?

106
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,760
You're not addicted to gaming, right?

107
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,920
No.

108
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,640
-It won't affect your studies, right?
-Of course not.

109
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,520
Good then.

110
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:04,040
Yuan, help look after them.
If you need anything, get it from me.

111
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:04,960
Yes, Dad.

112
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,760
Thank you!

113
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:10,040
Come here. Let's take your measurements.

114
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,280
Fuang.

115
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:14,040
Why are you still awake?
Don't you have a pitch with Cent tomorrow?

116
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,160
Go to bed.

117
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,920
-Time to rest.
-I'm going soon.

118
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,960
-I'll finish this last one.
-Mom.

119
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:23,120
I just came to give you a hug
for some encouragement.

120
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,840
What's up?

121
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,320
-Mom.
-Yes?

122
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,440
I'm going to work hard

123
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,080
and make a lot of money.

124
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,640
I'll get rich fast,

125
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,320
so you won't have to struggle anymore.

126
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,160
Money is important, Fuang,

127
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,200
but your happiness is even more important.

128
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:57,680
If you have to work just to earn money

129
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,200
without being happy,

130
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,520
I'm not okay with that.

131
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,000
Mom.

132
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,440
My happiness

133
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:18,200
is seeing you and Dad happy.

134
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:26,440
Even if I have to work really hard,
I'm okay with it.

135
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,120
Tomorrow,

136
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:34,040
I'm going to nail

137
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,520
the pitch with Cent.

138
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,000
I'm going to get rich!

139
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:49,240
Thank you, Fuang.

140
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,160
I just hope you get rich

141
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,640
doing what you love.

142
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:59,000
Because if you're doing what you love,

143
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:03,280
even if it's hard, you'll still be happy.

144
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,840
Okay?

145
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,320
Yes, Mom.

146
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:18,800
Keep going, sweetheart.

147
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,560
What?

148
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,200
Hey, Fuang.

149
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:39,080
How did you find out
that you liked drawing?

150
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,040
How did you know what you wanted to be?

151
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:44,520
At first, I didn't really know.

152
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:47,920
I started by liking comics.

153
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:52,200
Then I wanted to draw
beautiful pictures like them.

154
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,840
<i>After drawing for a while,</i>

155
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,880
<i>it started to feel fun,</i>
<i>and it made me happy.</i>

156
00:11:57,480 --> 00:12:01,040
<i>Like being in the right place, you know?</i>

157
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,640
<i>Like it's our space.</i>

158
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,080
<i>Why are you asking?</i>

159
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,560
I just wanted to know.

160
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,920
Nothing else. That's all.

161
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,760
What's up with him?

162
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,640
<i>Franc!</i>

163
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:19,680
Franc!

164
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,640
-Franc, look at this!
-Franc, dear!

165
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,400
-Mom!
-Look at this!

166
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,360
-Wow! Franc!
-Franc!

167
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:28,000
-Franc!
-Franc, dear!

168
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,760
-Franc, look at this!
-Hey, Franc!

169
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,480
Have you seen my IG likes yet?

170
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,440
But I have even more!

171
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:39,320
On Facebook, it's got hundreds
of thousands of likes and shares.

172
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,040
Look at this, dear!

173
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:44,080
Every Facebook page is posting about you.

174
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:46,440
-It's trending on Twitter too!
-Really?

175
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:48,400
#NoGoodbye

176
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,400
#FrancPeace

177
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,080
PITIFUL BRIDE-TO-BE BREAKS DOWN
AS WEDDING TURNS INTO A FUNERAL

178
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:54,720
This is really big news.

179
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,800
Franc, you're famous now!

180
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,200
-Look!
-Whoa!

181
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,840
-A hundred thousand followers!
-Over a hundred thousand already?

182
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,600
Oh my God!

183
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:07,480
Hey. You've been famous
since school, haven't you?

184
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:11,680
People were secretly taking your photos
and posting them on Facebook and IG.

185
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:14,320
Even in uni, you already had
tens of thousands of followers.

186
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,240
But it's not the same.

187
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:19,680
They liked how I looked,
but now they like my story.

188
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,480
You've always had
plenty of stories anyway.

189
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,880
Hey, I've gotta go.
I need to rush to my pitch.

190
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,120
What pitch? You've got a job now?

191
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,480
I'll tell you after I close the deal.

192
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,160
Wait! Who are you pitching to?

193
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,760
-Gotta go now. Bye!
-Hey, wait!

194
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:47,520
I don't know.
I haven't even talked to Fuang yet.

195
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,640
That's it. I'm sleepy.

196
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:57,520
Sleepy? It's almost noon!

197
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:59,040
Geez!

198
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,080
Bonus!

199
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:13,920
BONUS

200
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,680
<i>How did you know?</i>

201
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,640
And why didn't you tell me?

202
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:25,080
You really didn't know, did you?

203
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,640
-Here.
-Thank you.

204
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,080
Fuang!

205
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,800
Aunt Eiang, hello!

206
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,560
Hello.

207
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,200
Have you been here long?

208
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:04,560
Not at all. Where did you go?

209
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,600
I didn't go anywhere.
I live just in the next alley.

210
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:11,640
Cent wants to be alone.
He likes being alone,

211
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,040
so he rented this place himself.

212
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:15,120
Confused, huh?

213
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,960
Don't be. Everyone
gets confused like this.

214
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:21,320
Don't ask why. I don't have an answer.

215
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:23,760
Come on. Let's go inside!

216
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,400
Cent!

217
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,600
Cent!

218
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:35,760
Hey, Cent! Where are you?

219
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,280
-Cent!
-Why are you early?

220
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,120
I didn't want to be late.

221
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,240
Being on time doesn't mean you're late.

222
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,400
So what?

223
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:48,160
It's better that she came early.
Let's get started. I'm ready!

224
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,440
-Mom, go wait outside.
-Huh?

225
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:52,960
Are you kicking me out?

226
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,920
How can you do that?
You won't let me listen?

227
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,640
If you want me to make the decision,

228
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:58,840
I'd like to hear her alone.

229
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,680
But I was the one who recommended her.
I need to hear it too.

230
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:04,200
What if you say something wrong to her?

231
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,560
-Mom, then--
-It's okay!

232
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:09,120
It's fine. It's really okay, Aunt.

233
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,560
I understand. I'm okay.

234
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:17,320
Alright. It's good that you understand.

235
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,400
I'll wait outside then.

236
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:24,000
You don't believe your own kid.
You only listen to others.

237
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:26,160
That mouth of yours!

238
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,480
Go for it, dear!

239
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,200
You have eight minutes. Start.

240
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,120
Start now?

241
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:44,760
Why do I have to repeat myself?

242
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,800
Okay. I'll start.

243
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,640
My name is Fuang, Palin--

244
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:56,480
Get to the point.
This isn't a classroom report.

245
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:58,240
No need to introduce yourself.
I'm not a teacher.

246
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:01,840
Okay.

247
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,640
When I was a kid, I had a dream.

248
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,319
I don't want to hear your dream.

249
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,040
I want the truth.

250
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,920
But what I want to do comes from my dream.

251
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,920
If you don't listen,
you won't see my passion,

252
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,119
and you won't understand
why I want to do this.

253
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,319
Keep it short.

254
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:23,000
Got it.

255
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,359
I'm an only child.

256
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:31,440
<i>I didn't really have friends as a kid.</i>
<i>I stayed home with my grandma.</i>

257
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,160
<i>My parents worked really hard.</i>

258
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:36,080
<i>I liked reading storybooks.</i>

259
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,640
<i>And as I got older,</i>
<i>I started reading comics.</i>

260
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,200
<i>Whenever I entered the world of comics,</i>

261
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,320
<i>I felt really happy.</i>

262
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,160
Like the characters in the comics

263
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,520
were my imaginary friends.

264
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,680
After reading a lot,
I started wanting to draw too.

265
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,720
So I began by copying from the books.

266
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,600
<i>My parents started buying me</i>
<i>coloring sets.</i>

267
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:03,560
<i>I went from copying drawings</i>
<i>to creating my own characters.</i>

268
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:05,040
It made me feel less lonely,

269
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:07,280
like I had friends everywhere.

270
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,400
<i>In today's society,</i>

271
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:13,280
<i>I see that more and more people</i>
<i>are feeling lonely.</i>

272
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,480
<i>Both kids and adults.</i>

273
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:17,720
<i>That's why I want</i>
<i>to create friends for them.</i>

274
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,880
This is a character I created.

275
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:27,840
Its name is D-mer.

276
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,680
D-mer represents people with dreams.

277
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:35,440
It's chubby and round.

278
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:38,760
And its movement

279
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:43,080
feels like it's floating in a dream.
The shapes are curves and circles,

280
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:46,480
because circles and curves
give a warm and friendly feeling.

281
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:52,640
But beyond floating, that floating feeling

282
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,160
also carries encouragement.

283
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,360
I also made D-mer into Line stickers.
I'll show you now.

284
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:13,800
They're basic Line stickers,
like saying "hello".

285
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,080
This one is drawing.

286
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:20,160
It is cheerful and bright.
This one is saying "thank you".

287
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,000
And other basic expressions,
like surprised

288
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:24,040
or happy.

289
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:27,120
It's meant to give people encouragement.

290
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,400
You said you want funding, right?

291
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:31,960
What for?

292
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,640
For D-mer merchandise.

293
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:37,280
Stickers, posters, postcards,

294
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:41,000
and other higher-cost items
to sell at events

295
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,440
or online.

296
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:45,240
I also want to turn D-mer
into an animation,

297
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:47,840
so it becomes like a star who never ages.

298
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:50,720
It can generate income for us for life.

299
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:52,960
Do you know

300
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,360
what qualities

301
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,520
a successful character should have?

302
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,240
Well…

303
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,440
Cute, memorable…

304
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,520
charming,

305
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:08,080
easy to draw, and…

306
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,680
-And…
-One, fully thought-out concept.

307
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:13,120
Two, strong supporting story.

308
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,880
Three, gender-neutral appeal.

309
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,680
Four, no violence or gore.

310
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:19,520
Five, instantly recognizable
and memorable.

311
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,400
Six, a clear and unique DNA.

312
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:31,880
How many of those
does your character actually have?

313
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,920
There are…

314
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,320
Only two. Number three and four.

315
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,920
The rest don't exist.

316
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,640
And more importantly,

317
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,840
it doesn't reflect who you are
in your work. That's it.

318
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,160
Time's up.

319
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:51,440
Wait!

320
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,200
Just give me one more minute.

321
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,920
I know my work isn't good enough yet,

322
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,720
but I've really put my heart into it.

323
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,080
It's something I've wanted to do
since I was a kid.

324
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,080
I trained really hard since university.

325
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,520
This is my work.

326
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,960
I've practiced everything,
drawing, painting,

327
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:20,160
figure drawing, portraits,

328
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,480
landscapes,

329
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:25,840
illustration. I've studied
composition too.

330
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,880
Actually, I started practicing
before university.

331
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:32,080
Even after graduating,
I'm still practicing. I'll keep doing it.

332
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,840
I won't stop improving myself.

333
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,480
-Beautiful.
-Huh?

334
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,680
So beautiful. You know that, right?

335
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,800
I mean, your drawing is beautiful.

336
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:59,200
I've had some praise from my teachers,
friends, and my parents.

337
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,360
Your fundamentals are strong.

338
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,920
You can work in many styles.

339
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,440
It's clear you've trained consistently.

340
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:12,240
My friends have said that too.

341
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:16,520
They say I can do many styles,
but I'm not outstanding in any one style.

342
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:19,240
It hurts being a jack of all trades.

343
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,360
Please continue, Cent.

344
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,040
Your friends are right.

345
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,440
But also not entirely.

346
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:40,320
To find your own direction,
you have to go through every style first.

347
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,480
Only then will you know
what you're best at.

348
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:46,280
Or you combine different styles
until it becomes your own.

349
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,720
Whoa.

350
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,800
He's actually pretty good.

351
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,720
I'll have my mom fund you.

352
00:22:58,640 --> 00:22:59,480
Huh?

353
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:03,920
But not now.

354
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,440
And not with this piece.

355
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:16,120
You need to rethink it
or develop a new version

356
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,080
that has the six qualities.
Do you remember?

357
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,600
Six qualities. I remember them.

358
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:24,480
Fully thought-out concept,
strong story, unisex appeal,

359
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:27,240
no violence, easy to remember,
and a clear unique DNA.

360
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,640
-Teacher's pet.
-Huh?

361
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:35,120
Do that, then come back and pitch again.

362
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,560
For the app research task,

363
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,240
work starts next week.

364
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:48,760
Yes, sure!

365
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:51,960
If there's anything
you need me to do, just tell me.

366
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:57,000
Thank you so much.
Thank you for listening to my dream.

367
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:58,720
Thank you for the compliment.

368
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,040
I mean, for saying
my drawing is beautiful.

369
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:05,600
Thank you. Thank you so much!

370
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:10,520
Sorry.

371
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:13,480
Thank you!

372
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:17,400
I'll pack up my work now.

373
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,320
Cent!

374
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:31,000
I have something for you.

375
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,640
What is it?

376
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:37,000
If you want to know, just open it.

377
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,640
Thank you again.

378
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,200
Well, goodbye.

379
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,240
Yes!

380
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,880
Fuang, how did it go?

381
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,320
It went well.
Cent seemed okay with it too.

382
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:10,680
Really?

383
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,440
I'm so happy for you! What's next?

384
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:16,280
I just need to improve it
and then pitch again.

385
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:19,000
If it gets approved, you can fund me.

386
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:21,400
-Really?
-Yes!

387
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,760
I'm so happy for you!

388
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:26,000
Thank you. Oh, and about your project,

389
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:27,560
he said we can start next week.

390
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:30,240
Great, that means it'll be done sooner.

391
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,160
Yes.

392
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,200
I should head home now.
I want to tell my parents the good news.

393
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:37,920
Sure! I'll walk you out.

394
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,120
Beautiful, right?

395
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:09,640
I mean the work, not the person.

396
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,120
You were eavesdropping, weren't you?

397
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,280
Yeah, I was.

398
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,720
And I'm surprised too.

399
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:20,200
How do you even know that?
Did you just make up those six points?

400
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:22,840
I didn't.

401
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:26,400
My clients in Japan
use characters as presenters a lot.

402
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:29,440
Some famous ones
have more influence than celebrities.

403
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:32,320
It's taken very seriously there,
so I studied it.

404
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,480
Good.

405
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:37,720
-Then you should take care of her project.
-Mom!

406
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,880
I already have so much work.

407
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:42,240
If you want to fund her,
you handle it yourself.

408
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:45,120
I don't know anything about it.
You have to help me.

409
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:47,640
Think of it as you working on the app
in exchange for shares.

410
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:50,320
And you'll help her project

411
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:51,840
as my son.

412
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,800
Mom!

413
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,680
Hey, listen!

414
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:58,960
Thank you, my dear son.

415
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,080
Mom!

416
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,920
Yay!

417
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:07,960
Let's celebrate!

418
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:13,200
-Not dipping it in sauce?
-I already did.

419
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:15,040
-Fuang.
-Yes?

420
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:17,520
I'm glad you get to work with Cent.

421
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,800
That kid is really something.
He's got vision.

422
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,320
I feel like he'll go far.

423
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:26,040
Wait! You're praising someone?

424
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:28,840
Hey, you haven't praised anyone in ages.

425
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:32,040
-Not even me!
-Huh?

426
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,320
You're usually biased against kids,

427
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:36,400
but now you're praising Cent.

428
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:38,400
That means this kid
must really be something.

429
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:40,280
It's not just praise, Mom.

430
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,240
Yesterday, Cent came to our house, right?

431
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,200
Dad was chatting and laughing with him,

432
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:45,440
having a great time.

433
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:49,240
He had his arm around him
and walked him out to the front.

434
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:51,320
And he even said

435
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,520
he's always wanted a son.

436
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,520
Wanted a son?

437
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,040
-Hey!
-At noon,

438
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:01,120
Franc called you

439
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,440
and told you to call her back.

440
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:05,680
-Geez!
-Oh, right!

441
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,200
I totally forgot.

442
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:10,000
It's fine. Let's celebrate first.
She can wait.

443
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:10,960
Okay.

444
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:14,240
Franc is really famous now.

445
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:17,720
My friends have been sending me
so many news articles about her.

446
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,000
And they've dug up her old photos…

447
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:22,840
What do they call it again?

448
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,240
Profile drop.

449
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:27,720
Yeah, profile drop.
They even dug up her old photos

450
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:30,520
from when she was a drum major
and cheerleader.

451
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:34,400
I've been busy preparing my pitch,

452
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,680
so I didn't check the news.

453
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,800
My friend is that famous now?

454
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,400
I should go ask for an autograph.

455
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:40,560
Oh.

456
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:45,080
Hey! What?

457
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:46,760
Where did my grilled pork go?

458
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:50,160
Dad!

459
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,520
Was that mine?

460
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:56,080
-Here, take a new one.
-No!

461
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:58,560
-I grilled that for a long time.
-No, wait.

462
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,520
-Take this one.
-Give it to Fuang.

463
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:01,760
Franc!

464
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,960
Why did you delete
the birthday photo on your IG

465
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:08,240
that had me and your friends in it?

466
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:13,720
People check my IG, so I delete
anything that doesn't look good.

467
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:14,800
Gotta keep up my image.

468
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,560
How does a photo with me
and your friends ruin your image?

469
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,600
You were chubby
and kind of ugly back then.

470
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:22,400
Chubby and kind of ugly?

471
00:29:22,480 --> 00:29:24,880
But you're prettier now!

472
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,400
Don't take it seriously.

473
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:29,120
Too late! Don't hit me
and then comfort me.

474
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,720
Hey, I didn't mean it like that.

475
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:33,400
I'll post a new one for you. Don't be mad.

476
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,120
Oh!

477
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,960
"I'll post a new one. Don't be mad."

478
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:44,920
Guys! Have you seen the news about me?

479
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,880
-We have!
-Come on!

480
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:50,520
-Who wouldn't see it?
-You are all over my feed.

481
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,280
You guys are so extra!

482
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:54,840
Let's change the topic.

483
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:58,120
Fuang, who did you pitch to?
What happened? Tell me!

484
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,560
The thing is…

485
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,280
What is it?

486
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:03,960
It's kind of a long story.

487
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:06,920
-I'll tell you when we meet.
-Hey, no way! Tell us now!

488
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,040
You're stalling again and not telling us.

489
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:12,480
-Just tell us! I wanna know already.
-Stop, you guys!

490
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:15,200
Don't talk over each other.
I can't hear anything!

491
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:19,160
Let's celebrate Fuang's success then.
My treat, okay?

492
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:22,080
Wow, Boss Pound!

493
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:26,120
I start my first day at work tomorrow.
Can we do the evening?

494
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:30,240
Alright, after work it is,
Mr. Factory Man. See you.

495
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:33,360
Tomorrow's my first day punching in.

496
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:37,240
So where are we meeting?

497
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,520
How about my place?

498
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:43,320
I just redid the house.

499
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:45,280
-Okay!
-Let's go!

500
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:48,320
When you guys come over,
I'll have Mom cook,

501
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,240
and I'll bake desserts for you guys.

502
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:52,200
-Sounds good!
-Okay!

503
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:55,280
Hey guys, I gotta go.
I have plans. See you!

504
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,160
-Huh?
-Your girlfriend's calling you?

505
00:30:57,240 --> 00:31:00,040
Yuan! If you don't have one,
just stay quiet.

506
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:01,440
Bye!

507
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:03,480
So savage!

508
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:05,960
-Fuang, you're really not gonna tell us?
-Nope.

509
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,080
You wouldn't know them anyway.

510
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,440
But Yuan and Bonus do.

511
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,240
-Huh?
-What?

512
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:14,960
If you wanna know, come pick me up,
Miss "All-Over-My-Feed" Franc.

513
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,440
-Gotta go. Bye!
-Wait, Fuang!

514
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,840
-Wait!
-I'm out too. Bye!

515
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,920
-Hey, Yuan!
-I'm off too. Bye!

516
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,440
Everyone's leaving. What the heck?

517
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,560
Please try the cake.

518
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:40,360
Bonus, where did you buy this cake?

519
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,640
From a shop near my house.

520
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,520
Is it good?

521
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,560
-It's delicious!
-Yes!

522
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,560
So good!

523
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:54,240
Rich, but not too sweet.
The texture is perfect.

524
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:56,040
Yes.

525
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:57,480
Oh, right!

526
00:31:57,560 --> 00:32:01,000
Tomorrow we're having
a teacher-parent event at school.

527
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:03,280
We don't have any desserts yet.

528
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,600
Can we order from that shop?

529
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:08,720
Yes, you can!

530
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:10,520
Yes.

531
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:12,800
Besides the chocolate cake,
what else do they have?

532
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:15,920
There's coconut cake,

533
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,440
toffee cake,

534
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:22,600
and prune cake too.
The prune cake is really good.

535
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,360
<i>Loving what you do</i>

536
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,720
<i>or doing what you love.</i>

537
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,480
Which is better?

538
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,600
I don't know.
I've never really thought about it.

539
00:32:31,680 --> 00:32:34,880
I just think, whatever I do, I love it.
Success will come eventually.

540
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:38,080
How's your first day at work? Excited?

541
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:39,560
A little.

542
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,120
I'll show you around the factory.

543
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:45,120
Hey, what time do we finish work?

544
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:46,960
Around 5 to 6 p.m.

545
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:48,120
What?

546
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:51,040
First day and you're already asking
when you get off?

547
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:53,840
No. I've got plans with my friends
at Bonus's house.

548
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,720
We're celebrating Fuang's new job.

549
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:59,120
Bonus's house is actually
not far from here.

550
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,440
Alright, I'll give you a ride.

551
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:02,760
Thanks.

552
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:06,360
Mr. Yong, Mr. Yuan,
Boss Yut is calling for you.

553
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,160
This brand has been working with us
for a long time.

554
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,440
It's their 13th anniversary this year.

555
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,240
I want you to think

556
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:24,240
of how we can make the shirt
look more special.

557
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:26,880
How about switching to a lighter fabric

558
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:28,800
that's water- and sweat-resistant?

559
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:30,920
I just got a new batch of fabric.

560
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:35,040
It'll raise the production cost a bit,
but I think it's worth it.

561
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,600
What if

562
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:44,040
we change the collar?

563
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:48,080
Well…

564
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:53,000
There's a trend right now,
a swallow neck collar.

565
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:56,440
The idea is they place the buttons

566
00:33:56,520 --> 00:34:00,320
under the collar.
It lifts the collar slightly, so it looks

567
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,240
more structured and not flat.

568
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:05,880
It gives a different feel
from a normal polo shirt.

569
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:08,120
It looks good

570
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:11,040
on its own, and it also works with a suit.

571
00:34:11,120 --> 00:34:13,639
If we change
both the fabric and the collar,

572
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,560
would it be difficult?

573
00:34:15,159 --> 00:34:16,199
Not really.

574
00:34:16,719 --> 00:34:18,719
We're not changing the whole design.

575
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:20,800
Just the collar and the fabric. That's it.

576
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:23,480
Alright! Take it to the client.

577
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:26,360
Yes. Mr. Yuan.

578
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,560
Could I get a photo of the collar

579
00:34:28,639 --> 00:34:30,159
you mentioned?

580
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:31,480
Sure, Aunt Phueng.

581
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,639
Here it is. I saved it from IG.

582
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:38,280
As Ralph said,

583
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:40,520
what he designed in 1967

584
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,040
shouldn't feel outdated.

585
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:44,840
And what he designed
last year shouldn't feel new.

586
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:47,960
This year or the next,
it makes no difference.

587
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:49,360
Fashion is cyclical.

588
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:57,400
Go prepare the quotation.
Bring it to me when it's done.

589
00:34:58,840 --> 00:34:59,960
Yes.

590
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:33,760
Thank you, bro.

591
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:35,720
Yuan!

592
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:39,280
-Hello, Yong.
-Hi.

593
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,800
Thank you for dropping Yuan off
all the way here.

594
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:43,560
No problem.

595
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:46,520
Haven't seen you in a while.
You've graduated. Are you working?

596
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:50,320
I'm working part-time
at a daycare right now,

597
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,040
waiting for my exam results
for a permanent job.

598
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:54,480
Alright then, let's say

599
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,160
you don't pass the exam.

600
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:59,160
The factory is hiring sewing staff.
If you're interested,

601
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,600
-just tell us.
-Whoa, Yuan!

602
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,080
I'm really bad at hands-on work.

603
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:05,960
I fail every exam.

604
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,160
But!

605
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:11,240
I'm okay with home economics.

606
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:15,120
Here! I just baked these fresh.

607
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:16,160
For me?

608
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,160
Please give them to your dad and mom too.

609
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:20,040
Thanks a lot.

610
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,240
-Pound's here.
-Oh.

611
00:36:24,120 --> 00:36:25,360
Alright, I'll head off then.

612
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:27,600
I'll have Yuan return the box to you.

613
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:28,880
Okay.

614
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,760
Hello, Yong.

615
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:33,640
Nice car, Pound.
Let's go for a drive sometime.

616
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:35,520
Sure, bro.

617
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:37,560
I'll head off. You kids chat.

618
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:39,520
-See you.
-Goodbye.

619
00:36:40,120 --> 00:36:42,040
-Drive safe.
-Thanks.

620
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:45,120
-Let's go inside.
-Come on.

621
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,120
Alright.

622
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:52,280
Guys, let's celebrate!

623
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:54,000
-Come on.
-Park the car!

624
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,120
Hey, let's eat. It's gonna burn!

625
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:59,000
-Come on.
-Coming!

626
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:01,360
-Here you go.
-Let's eat!

627
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:03,240
It's gonna burn!

628
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:06,120
-Eat a lot, okay?
-Eat as much as you want.

629
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,040
We're done already.

630
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:09,120
Come again often.

631
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:13,600
-Yes, come visit often.
-Sure, thank you!

632
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:15,480
Hey.

633
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:18,000
Let's get to the point.

634
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:21,760
So, Fuang, what exactly
did you pitch today?

635
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,120
And who did you pitch it to?

636
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:28,480
<i>I found someone to replace Peace</i>
<i>in helping with my mom's work.</i>

637
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:30,800
I'm planning to start the project soon.

638
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:33,080
But before that,

639
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:35,560
I'll go see you in Japan
and wrap things up.

640
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:38,920
I want to talk to you
about the shares you're selling.

641
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,600
I might buy them myself.

642
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:48,880
But I think you should keep
your money for now, Cent.

643
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:52,840
Even if you get my shares,
it still won't be half.

644
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,960
But if you get your mom's shares,

645
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:56,920
you'll become the major shareholder

646
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,960
<i>without even needing mine.</i>

647
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:02,000
<i>And honestly, Cent,</i>

648
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:05,840
if I sell to you, I can't bring myself
to charge too much.

649
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:08,880
But if I sell to someone else,
I can set the full price.

650
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:12,280
Yeah.

651
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:13,760
I understand.

652
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:18,400
It's fine. We'll talk later.

653
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:20,520
Oh, right! So…

654
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:25,840
So who's your assistant again?

655
00:38:27,080 --> 00:38:28,320
The daughter of my mom's friend.

656
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:30,760
The daughter of your mom's friend?

657
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,480
Are you okay with it?

658
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:36,880
Yeah, I'm fine. She's kind of weird.

659
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:39,000
Weird?

660
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:41,440
You say she's weird.

661
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:45,960
Whoa, she must be really weird then.

662
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:47,960
Is it a guy or a girl?

663
00:38:58,280 --> 00:39:00,840
-A girl.
<i>-Huh?</i>

664
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:03,240
<i>A girl?</i>

665
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,040
Yeah, that's it. See you. I've got work.

666
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:12,040
Wait! Cent, who is she? Cent!

667
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:14,600
What?

668
00:39:15,640 --> 00:39:17,480
He's working with a girl?

669
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,760
Who is Cent? Why do you all know him?

670
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:22,440
Why am I the only one who doesn't?

671
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:26,120
We met him when Peace set up

672
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:27,560
your surprise proposal meeting.

673
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:29,640
-That's why you didn't meet him.
-Right.

674
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:33,360
So basically,

675
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:36,480
you got a job as his assistant,
working on the app for his mom.

676
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:38,760
Yeah.

677
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:41,360
But that's just a paid job.

678
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,360
The highlight is,

679
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:46,280
I told him about my dream project,

680
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,680
and he agreed to invest.

681
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:50,760
If I pass my next pitch,

682
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:54,440
I might get to start a small company
and turn my dream into reality.

683
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,240
-That's awesome!
-Nice!

684
00:40:08,960 --> 00:40:11,040
The Cent you guys saw, he seems

685
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:13,160
kind of weird, right?

686
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:15,680
But I don't think he's an ordinary guy.

687
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:19,040
Well, he…

688
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:22,360
Everything he says hits hard.

689
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,560
I was so stunned, I couldn't argue back.

690
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:26,240
He's friends with Peace.

691
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:28,400
I think he's probably not an ordinary guy.

692
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,440
-Yeah.
-I agree.

693
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:36,320
The only comment I have about him

694
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:37,280
is…

695
00:40:41,720 --> 00:40:43,720
-He's so hot!
-Bonus!

696
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:48,920
He really is hot.

697
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:50,440
His face is really clean-looking,

698
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:53,640
and his style is super minimalist.

699
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:55,560
But it's like a luxury minimalist vibe.

700
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,680
The best part is, it gives him

701
00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:00,720
a classy, effortlessly cool vibe.

702
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:02,800
Whoa, you're exaggerating!

703
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:04,320
I'm not!

704
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:06,640
Anyway,

705
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:09,960
that's everything about me. I'm leaving.

706
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:12,200
-Hey!
-Wait!

707
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,520
You can't just leave like that!

708
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:14,680
-Yeah!
-Why leave now?

709
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:17,040
I still have to bring desserts to Cent.

710
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:19,880
-Come on!
-Bringing desserts to Cent.

711
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:21,320
Aw!

712
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:23,040
Don't tease me like that.

713
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,920
-Stop it!
-Wait!

714
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:26,480
Your parents know each other.

715
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:30,080
Is there something going on?

716
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:34,320
No way! I'm heading off now.

717
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:37,480
This meal was great. I'll take that.

718
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:39,000
-Huh?
-Bye.

719
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:42,040
-You're really leaving?
-Want me to give you a ride?

720
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:43,120
It's okay.

721
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:44,920
I already booked a car. Thanks a lot.

722
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,080
-Get home safe.
-Bye.

723
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:48,200
-She really is leaving.
-Yeah.

724
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:52,480
Guys, I'm heading out too.
I don't want to stay up late.

725
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:54,360
My face will age. I'm out. Bye.

726
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:56,080
Hey!

727
00:41:56,160 --> 00:41:58,080
-Drive safe!
-Yeah.

728
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,840
I'll walk them out.

729
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,680
What? Everyone's leaving.

730
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:05,800
What the heck?
They leave whenever they want.

731
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,600
What are you doing?

732
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:29,440
I was worried about Fuang. It was dark,
so I wanted to drop her off at home.

733
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:31,720
Such a hero.

734
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:38,400
Why are you mocking me?

735
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:41,280
I'm not mocking you.
I just want to remind you.

736
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:44,240
What reminder do I need
just to drop a friend off?

737
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:46,120
Just self-awareness.

738
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:49,000
That you only wanted to drop her off,
not anything else.

739
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,360
Honestly, Bonus,

740
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:54,360
I'm getting sick of you.
You keep beating around the bush.

741
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:56,480
Be straight with me. What's your problem?

742
00:42:57,960 --> 00:43:00,040
You want to see Cent, don't you?

743
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:06,960
I don't even know him.
Why would I want to meet him?

744
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:10,840
Maybe it's the way he comes across.

745
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:13,600
You heard Fuang praising him.

746
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:16,720
He sounded good, like a big name,
so you got curious.

747
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:18,440
Right?

748
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:22,880
-You're way too biased against me.
-Yeah.

749
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:26,120
I'll be straight with you.

750
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:28,440
About you secretly dating Peace

751
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:30,920
and acting like you didn't know
Fuang liked him,

752
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:32,760
I don't believe it.

753
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,480
-Want more?
-Hey, stop!

754
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:39,920
-Come on!
-They're so funny!

755
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:41,720
Want some? Want it?

756
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,680
-I'm good!
-You're not eating anymore?

757
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:45,560
<i>I let it go because we're friends.</i>

758
00:43:45,640 --> 00:43:48,880
I pretended nothing happened,
like it didn't matter.

759
00:43:50,880 --> 00:43:53,840
But if it happens again this time,
I won't ignore it.

760
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:56,240
Fuang is a good person.

761
00:43:56,320 --> 00:44:00,480
She doesn't say it, but I know she's hurt.
She does everything for her friends.

762
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:02,840
Is Fuang only your friend?

763
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:05,400
She's my friend too.

764
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:09,480
If I knew she was hurt, I wouldn't do it.
Remember what I'm saying!

765
00:44:49,360 --> 00:44:51,600
Sorry for just opening the door
and coming in.

766
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:57,400
My mom told me to bring this

767
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:00,000
as a thank you gift for hiring me.

768
00:45:00,600 --> 00:45:03,480
I'm sorry for coming this late
without telling you first.

769
00:45:03,560 --> 00:45:06,280
I was going to call you, but I couldn't.
I don't have your number.

770
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:07,720
You done?

771
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:11,120
Yes.

772
00:45:25,040 --> 00:45:26,200
I'll head back now.

773
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:28,200
Take it back with you.

774
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:32,360
-Yes?
-I don't feel like washing it.

775
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:34,640
Huh?

776
00:45:57,680 --> 00:45:58,800
What are you looking for?

777
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:02,240
A plate.

778
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:08,640
But I forgot there aren't any.

779
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:10,560
No plates?

780
00:46:13,640 --> 00:46:16,800
Sorry, I forgot
you don't like repeating things.

781
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:37,600
Wait!

782
00:46:37,680 --> 00:46:38,720
Hold on!

783
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:42,600
Put it down first. Don't touch it yet.

784
00:46:44,560 --> 00:46:47,200
Putting the cookies on tissue like that,

785
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,800
it doesn't look appetizing.

786
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:54,040
Alright, hang on a second.

787
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,080
Let me wash my hands.

788
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:52,960
There you go. Enjoy.

789
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:56,560
-This box--
-It's okay.

790
00:47:56,640 --> 00:47:57,720
I'll wash it later.

791
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:03,800
I'll wash it.

792
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:09,680
I'm going to Japan for a couple of days.

793
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:12,480
I'll need to push back
your start date a bit.

794
00:48:16,320 --> 00:48:17,320
Understood.

795
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:20,320
While I wait,
I'll develop the character design

796
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:21,880
and come back with a new proposal.

797
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:33,040
Anything else? You can go now.
I've got work to do.

798
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:41,120
I feel bad asking,
but it's already late and…

799
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:42,480
So?

800
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:47,160
Well…

801
00:48:48,240 --> 00:48:49,440
Could I use your bathroom?

802
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:56,360
Thank you.

803
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:41,400
I'll head back now. Thank you.

804
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:49,320
Cent!

805
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:52,880
Cent!

806
00:49:55,320 --> 00:49:56,720
You should go to the bathroom.

807
00:49:57,560 --> 00:49:58,400
Huh?

808
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:01,720
I don't mean to pry, but I understand.

809
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:04,520
My dad is like that too.
When he's editing and refuses to get up,

810
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:08,440
and when he really needs to pee,
he shakes his leg like you do.

811
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:14,520
So I just guessed you probably need to go.

812
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:25,560
You can go now.

813
00:50:43,440 --> 00:50:47,320
Cent, I know you hate repetition,
but if you're holding your pee,

814
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:49,320
-you will--
-Okay!

815
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:52,760
I'm going to the bathroom. Happy now?

816
00:50:53,960 --> 00:50:55,240
You can go home.

817
00:50:57,760 --> 00:50:59,040
Bye!

818
00:51:00,280 --> 00:51:02,040
Don't hold it in again!

819
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:15,040
<i>When you need to pee, go pee!</i>

820
00:51:15,120 --> 00:51:16,360
<i>The downside of holding it in</i>

821
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:19,320
<i>is that it can lead</i>
<i>to bladder inflammation.</i>

822
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:20,840
<i>How many times has this happened already?</i>

823
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:22,920
<i>Urinary tract infection,</i>

824
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:25,200
<i>kidney stones, acne,</i>

825
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:26,880
<i>body odor!</i>

826
00:51:34,440 --> 00:51:36,800
Mom!

827
00:51:40,240 --> 00:51:41,360
<i>Hello.</i>

828
00:51:41,440 --> 00:51:42,800
<i>Hello, Miss Franc.</i>

829
00:51:42,880 --> 00:51:47,920
<i>This is Pie from the team</i>
<i>behind your surprise proposal with Peace.</i>

830
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,840
<i>A TV program contacted us</i>

831
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:52,680
<i>asking for footage from the event</i>
<i>to air on their show.</i>

832
00:51:52,760 --> 00:51:54,280
<i>Would that be okay?</i>

833
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:58,680
I don't mind.

834
00:51:58,760 --> 00:52:02,280
But I was actually planning
to post the video on my Instagram.

835
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:07,520
If the program wants to take it
from my IG instead,

836
00:52:07,600 --> 00:52:08,640
that's fine.

837
00:52:08,720 --> 00:52:11,720
<i>Sure. I'll inform the program.</i>

838
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:14,600
<i>-Thank you.</i>
-Yes, of course.

839
00:52:45,480 --> 00:52:50,000
EVERYTHING I EVER DREAMED OF
UNTIL IT ALL SHATTERED

840
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:55,600
#FRANCPEACE #NOGOODBYE #CANTSTOPCRYING

841
00:52:55,680 --> 00:53:00,160
SO SAD FOR YOU, FRANC
SENDING YOU STRENGTH, FRANC

842
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:01,680
OMG I'M CRYING
SUCH A BEAUTIFUL CLIP BUT SO HEARTBREAKING

843
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:04,680
SAD, IT HURTS

844
00:53:04,760 --> 00:53:06,320
SO HEARTBREAKING

845
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:07,720
TEARS ARE FALLING
SENDING YOU STRENGTH, LOVE YOU

846
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:09,080
SENDING HUGS, I'M ROOTING FOR YOU
KEEP GOING, SIS

847
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:13,400
YOU HAVE ONE NEW MESSAGE

848
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:16,560
HELLO, FRANC
I'M REACHING OUT FROM AN AGENCY

849
00:53:16,640 --> 00:53:20,320
<i>Hello, Franc. I'm reaching out</i>
<i>from an agency.</i>

850
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:25,480
An agency?

851
00:54:15,120 --> 00:54:15,960
MADE TENS OF THOUSANDS IN STOCKS
LET'S MEET UP! WANT TO TREAT YOU TO WAGYU

852
00:54:16,040 --> 00:54:17,600
<i>Made tens of thousands in stocks.</i>

853
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:19,480
<i>Let's meet up!</i>

854
00:54:19,560 --> 00:54:21,000
<i>Want to treat you to wagyu.</i>

855
00:54:31,280 --> 00:54:33,880
Dad, Mom, I've got something
I want to ask you guys.

856
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,840
I need to talk to you about something too.

857
00:54:38,680 --> 00:54:40,080
Okay then.

858
00:54:40,600 --> 00:54:43,760
Let me go first. It's a great idea!

859
00:54:43,840 --> 00:54:45,440
I got it from the Hua Hin trip.

860
00:54:46,160 --> 00:54:47,120
Well,

861
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,240
I'm going to turn the house
into income, Dad.

862
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:51,240
-Here's the plan--
-Enough!

863
00:54:52,680 --> 00:54:54,520
I'm going to sell that house.

864
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:56,880
Sell?

865
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:58,520
Why would you sell it, Dad?

866
00:55:01,440 --> 00:55:02,440
Well…

867
00:55:03,880 --> 00:55:05,440
I was about to tell you.

868
00:55:11,400 --> 00:55:13,080
Go find a job.

869
00:55:14,880 --> 00:55:18,400
Stop drifting around
and wasting money day after day.

870
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:22,920
Dad, wait!

871
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:25,760
Get a job?

872
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:30,880
What do you mean? I don't get it.
We already have a family business.

873
00:55:30,960 --> 00:55:32,200
Also,

874
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:35,840
I was planning to help at our factory.

875
00:55:35,920 --> 00:55:38,080
Why would I need another job?
No, I'm not doing that.

876
00:55:39,320 --> 00:55:42,920
Pound! Don't keep questioning your dad.

877
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:45,120
If he told you to get a job,
then go get one.

878
00:55:45,200 --> 00:55:46,840
I can't not ask, Mom!

879
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:50,160
I already had a plan, Dad.

880
00:55:50,240 --> 00:55:52,640
I've planned out a lot of business ideas.

881
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:54,960
Our paper factory

882
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:57,600
should shift to the e-commerce market.

883
00:55:57,680 --> 00:55:59,800
Right now, eco-friendly trends are rising.

884
00:56:00,320 --> 00:56:02,640
Delivery businesses are booming, Dad.

885
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:06,240
Yes, there was COVID before.

886
00:56:06,320 --> 00:56:09,840
-If we push a little longer, we won't--
-Stop it!

887
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:14,560
I don't have time to listen
to this nonsense of yours.

888
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:18,240
The business world isn't as easy
as you're making it sound.

889
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:20,440
And I've never once told you

890
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:22,880
that I'd let you work at the factory.

891
00:56:28,200 --> 00:56:29,040
That's enough.

892
00:56:33,560 --> 00:56:35,000
Everything I teach you,

893
00:56:35,080 --> 00:56:37,200
I've tried it myself. It works.

894
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:39,960
I became rich. You can become rich too.

895
00:56:40,040 --> 00:56:41,640
-Rich!
-Rich!

896
00:56:49,360 --> 00:56:51,960
Cent's office is really grand!

897
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:54,200
He must be really rich.

898
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:55,200
No, wait.

899
00:56:55,800 --> 00:56:57,440
Super rich!

900
00:56:57,520 --> 00:56:58,680
Cent.

901
00:56:59,880 --> 00:57:01,920
If you don't learn to keep an open mind,

902
00:57:03,040 --> 00:57:04,160
one day,

903
00:57:05,160 --> 00:57:07,240
you might lose everything.

904
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:53,600
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
